            <h3 class="mb-3">1. Customer Onboarding Process</h3>
            <p>
                The system begins with the Customer Onboarding process. 
                In this step, a new customer is added by entering personal details, 
                KYC information, contact details, nominee details, and required documents 
                such as photo, signature, and identity proofs.
            </p>
            <p>
                After successful submission, the customer profile is created and stored 
                securely in the system for further banking operations.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">2. Account Creation (Saving / Current)</h3>
            <p>
                Once the customer is added, a Saving Account or Current Account can be created 
                based on customer requirements. The account is linked directly to the customer profile.
            </p>
            <p>
                All account-related details such as account number, branch, balance, 
                and transaction history are maintained automatically by the system.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">3. Customer Approval & Loan Eligibility</h3>
            <p>
                After verification, the customer profile is reviewed and approved by the admin.
                Only approved customers become eligible for further financial services.
            </p>
            <p>
                Once approved, customers can apply for various loan products directly 
                from their account profile.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">4. Loan Services</h3>
            <p>
                The system supports multiple loan services to fulfill customer financial needs.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                <li>Personal Loan</li>
                <li>Group Loan</li>
                <li>Gold Loan</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Loan applications, approvals, EMI schedules, interest calculations, 
                and repayment tracking are managed digitally.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">5. Policy & Deposit Schemes</h3>
            <p>
                Customers can also invest in various deposit and saving policies offered by the bank.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                <li>Recurring Deposit (RD)</li>
                <li>Fixed Deposit (FD)</li>
                <li>Daily Deposit (DD)</li>
                <li>Monthly Income Scheme (MIS)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                All policy details, maturity amount, tenure, and interest calculations 
                are handled automatically by the system.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">6. Accounts & Financial Management</h3>
            <p>
                The system provides complete account management features for financial tracking.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                <li>Ledger Management</li>
                <li>Incoming Payments</li>
                <li>Outgoing Payments</li>
                <li>Balance Sheet Management</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                This ensures transparency, accuracy, and real-time financial reporting.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">7. Employees & Team Incentives</h3>
            <p>
                Employee and Team Member management is integrated into the system.
                Incentives and commissions are calculated based on performance, 
                customer acquisition, and financial activities.
            </p>
            <p>
                This helps in motivating employees and maintaining performance transparency.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">8. Financial Consultants (Agents)</h3>
            <p>
                The system also supports Financial Consultants (Agents).
                Each customer can be assigned a dedicated Financial Consultant 
                who assists them with banking, loans, and policy-related services.
            </p>
            <p>
                Consultant-wise customer tracking and incentive calculation 
                are available within the system.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">9. Reports & Analytics</h3>
            <p>
                The system provides detailed report generation for administrative 
                and banking purposes.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                <li>Customer Reports</li>
                <li>Account & Transaction Reports</li>
                <li>Loan Reports</li>
                <li>Policy & Deposit Reports</li>
                <li>Financial & Balance Sheet Reports</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Reports can be generated anytime for auditing, analysis, 
                and official banking documentation.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="mb-3">10. System Objective</h3>
            <p>
                The objective of this system is to provide a complete, secure, 
                and efficient digital banking solution that covers customer management, 
                financial operations, loan processing, policy management, 
                employee incentives, and reporting under one platform.
            </p>

